		<official-title>To prohibit certain closures of Senior Reserve Officers’ Training Corps programs of the Army.</official-title>
	</form>
	<legis-body id="HC36C463C03CE4B2FA1D111576925C666" style="OLC">
		<section id="H90E541747B4C4011B0FBF2802AD108B1" section-type="section-one">
      <enum>1.</enum>
      <header>Short title</header>
      <text display-inline="no-display-inline">This Act may be cited as the 
          <quote>
          <short-title>
              <cato:entity-ref xmlns:cato="http://namespaces.cato.org/catoxml" entity-type="act" value="Readying Our Troops for Combat Act of 2014" proposed="true">Readying Our Troops for Combat Act of 2014</cato:entity-ref>
            </short-title>
        </quote> or the <quote>
            <cato:entity-ref xmlns:cato="http://namespaces.cato.org/catoxml" entity-type="act" value="ROTC Act of 2014" proposed="true">ROTC Act of 2014</cato:entity-ref>
          </quote>.
      </text>
		</section>
    <section id="H0C668EE7D6004705985219B6693C2B04">
      <enum>2.</enum>
      <header>Prohibition of closures of Senior ROTC programs of the Army</header>
      <text display-inline="no-display-inline">During the period beginning on the date of the enactment of this Act and ending on July 1, 2020,
			 the <cato:entity-ref xmlns:cato="http://namespaces.cato.org/catoxml" entity-id="2100" entity-type="federal-body">Secretary of the Army</cato:entity-ref> may not, pursuant to <cato:entity-ref xmlns:cato="http://namespaces.cato.org/catoxml" entity-id="9700" entity-type="federal-body">Department of Defense</cato:entity-ref>
			 Instruction 1215.08, disestablish, or initiate the disestablishment of, a
			 Senior Reserve Officers’ Training Corps program of the Army established
			 pursuant to <cato:entity-ref xmlns:cato="http://namespaces.cato.org/catoxml" entity-type="uscode" value="usc-chapter/10/103">
          <external-xref legal-doc="usc-chapter" parsable-cite="usc-chapter/10/103">chapter 103</external-xref> of title 10, United States Code</cato:entity-ref>.</text>
		</section>
